      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structADC__AnalogWDGConfTypeDef_1a025e81af21b93c5b8daf9f5241383302" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>uint32_t</type>
        <definition>uint32_t ADC_AnalogWDGConfTypeDef::WatchdogNumber</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>WatchdogNumber</name>
        <qualifiedname>ADC_AnalogWDGConfTypeDef::WatchdogNumber</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Select which ADC analog watchdog is monitoring the selected channel. For Analog Watchdog 1: Only 1 channel can be monitored (or overall group of channels by setting parameter &apos;WatchdogMode&apos;) For Analog Watchdog 2 and 3: Several channels can be monitored (by successive calls of &apos;<ref refid="group__ADC__Exported__Functions__Group3_1ga7e992cf20f0fdc90cf558bc13dd6995c" kindref="member">HAL_ADC_AnalogWDGConfig()</ref>&apos; for each channel) This parameter can be a value of <ref refid="group__ADC__HAL__EC__AWD__NUMBER" kindref="compound">Analog watchdog - ADC analog watchdog (AWD) number</ref>. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" line="328" column="12" bodyfile="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" bodystart="328" bodyend="-1"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structADC__AnalogWDGConfTypeDef_1ad4c60783321a30e8edffa323148e424d" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>uint32_t</type>
        <definition>uint32_t ADC_AnalogWDGConfTypeDef::WatchdogMode</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>WatchdogMode</name>
        <qualifiedname>ADC_AnalogWDGConfTypeDef::WatchdogMode</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Configure the ADC analog watchdog mode: single/all/none channels. For Analog Watchdog 1: Configure the ADC analog watchdog mode: single channel or all channels, ADC groups regular and-or injected. For Analog Watchdog 2 and 3: Several channels can be monitored by applying successively the AWD init structure. Channels on ADC group regular and injected are not differentiated: Set value &apos;ADC_ANALOGWATCHDOG_SINGLE_xxx&apos; to monitor 1 channel, value &apos;ADC_ANALOGWATCHDOG_ALL_xxx&apos; to monitor all channels, &apos;ADC_ANALOGWATCHDOG_NONE&apos; to monitor no channel. This parameter can be a value of <ref refid="group__ADC__analog__watchdog__mode" kindref="compound">ADC analog watchdog (AWD) mode</ref>. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" line="335" column="12" bodyfile="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" bodystart="335" bodyend="-1"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structADC__AnalogWDGConfTypeDef_1abc86b5861e3eff802fe765e62054f348" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>uint32_t</type>
        <definition>uint32_t ADC_AnalogWDGConfTypeDef::Channel</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>Channel</name>
        <qualifiedname>ADC_AnalogWDGConfTypeDef::Channel</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Select which ADC channel to monitor by analog watchdog. For Analog Watchdog 1: this parameter has an effect only if parameter &apos;WatchdogMode&apos; is configured on single channel (only 1 channel can be monitored). For Analog Watchdog 2 and 3: Several channels can be monitored. To use this feature, call successively the function <ref refid="group__ADC__Exported__Functions__Group3_1ga7e992cf20f0fdc90cf558bc13dd6995c" kindref="member">HAL_ADC_AnalogWDGConfig()</ref> for each channel to be added (or removed with value &apos;ADC_ANALOGWATCHDOG_NONE&apos;). This parameter can be a value of <ref refid="group__ADC__HAL__EC__CHANNEL" kindref="compound">ADC instance - Channel number</ref>. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" line="347" column="12" bodyfile="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" bodystart="347" bodyend="-1"/>
      </memberdef>
